			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">LS; Sulfonated lignin; SL</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">LS; Sulfonated lignin; SL</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Inorganic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Lignosulfonates (LS) are water-soluble anionic polyelectrolyte polymers that are byproducts from the production of wood pulp using sulfite pulping. They are used in many technical applications, such as plasticizers, dispersants, stabilizers, and agrochemical formulations. Lignin sulfonate is a brown powder consisting of a sulfonate salt made from waste liquor of the sulfate pulping process of soft wood. It is used in concrete, leather tanning, as an additive in oil-well drilling mud, and as a source of vanillin.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">木质素磺酸盐（LS）是一种水溶性阴离子聚电解质聚合物，是使用亚硫酸盐制浆法生产木浆的副产品。它们可用于多种技术用途，如增塑剂、分散剂、稳定剂和农用化学品配方。木质素磺酸盐是一种棕色粉末，由软木硫酸盐制浆过程中产生的废液中的磺酸盐盐组成。它可用于混凝土、皮革鞣制、油井钻井泥浆添加剂以及香兰素的来源。</common:generalComment>
